;\\n\\n        assertThat(defaultValue).isNull();\\n    }\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"\\n    public static final class ConstructibleType {\\n        public ConstructibleType() {\\n        }\\n\\n        String value() {\\n            return \\\"created\\\";\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static final class MultiConstructorType {\\n        public MultiConstructorType() {\\n        }\\n\\n        public MultiConstructorType(String ignored) {\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class IntrospectedType {\\n        private final String name = \\\"example\\\";\\n        private final int count = 1;\\n\\n        String name() {\\n            return name;\\n        }\\n\\n        int count() {\\n            return count;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\\n    private @interface DefaultChoice {\\n    }\\n\\n    private enum Choice {\\n        FIRST,\\n        @DefaultChoice\\n        SECOND\\n    }\\n\", \"newText\": \"\\n\"}]}\n../3007-b10f0dbb/human-intervention-logs/org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T11-32-30-261705Z.log:2915:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating constructor inclusion**\\n\\nI’m looking into how `GetConstructors` calls `getDeclaredConstructors` on `Ctor.class` and filters included ones while asserting the parameter count is one. For the `findConstructor/createInstance`, I’m focusing on getting the default public constructor for `ClassUtil` and ensuring it excludes ordinary test classes. I realize I need to modify some imports — removing `RetentionPolicy` while using `java.lang.annotation.Retention` instead. I might also need to adjust by removing nested classes and unnecessary items like `Constructible`.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0a2cc192c065305d0169f7322b92bc8196b23e353bf58559a6\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_conte